title: Doucette leads Neelin to victory
text:
Doucette leads Neelin to victory By: Uncredited Enlarge Image 
Crocus Plainsmen’s Bryanna Sutlic, right, leaps to hit the ball past the block of Neelin Spartans’ Savannah Doucette during a varsity girls’ volleyball match on Tuesday. (BRUCE BUMSTEAD/BRANDON SUN) 
Savannah Doucette had 10 kills and three blocks as she led the host Neelin Spartans to a 3-1 victory over the Crocus Plainsmen on Tuesday in a varsity girls’ match in the Westman High School Volleyball League. 
The Neelin girls, who defeated Crocus 259, 2426, 2518, 2520, also received six kills from Madison Hayden. 
Bryanna Sutlic had seven kills and one ace for Crocus, while Brynn Pedlow had five kills. 
In Virden, Carmen Ross led the Golden Bears varsity girls with 23 kills and Avery Hayward contributed 10 kills as they beat the Vincent Massey Vikings (3-1) 25-20, 18-25, 25-13, 25-22. No stats were available from Vincent Massey. 
In varsity boys’ play, Crocus beat Neelin 3-0, while Virden swept Vincent Massey. 
At Neelin, Jordan Phillips had three kills and two blocks, while Steven Fawcett had two kills and four blocks as Crocus won 25-15, 25-20, 25-17. Dylan Foster had five kills, and Sean Coey had four kills and two blocks for Neelin 
In Virden, Austin Watts had five kills, and Ruben Warkentin had three blocks as Virden won 25-7, 25-18, 25-11. Carter Hyra had six kills and eight digs, while Roman Zaliskyy had five kills and three blocks for Massey.
